The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Help for exporters
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Help for exporters
          OUR BUREAU                              
	Calcutta, Aug. 9: The government today assured that measures would be taken to address exporters concerns, including refund of taxes, at the earliest.         
	Domestic exporters are facing problems on the issue of tax refunds, and the introduction of goods and services tax in 2010 will address the problem to a great extent, external affairs ministers Pranab Mukherjee said here today.        
	Nalco award        
	National Aluminium Company Limited (Nalco), a leading manufacturer of alumina and aluminium, has bagged the EEPCs All India Export Award for its export performance during 2006-07.        
	The minister, who was speaking at the awards function of the Engineering Export Promotion Council of India (EEPC) here, said trade infrastructure needed to be upgraded.                                                                                                                                      
